The paper deals with coreference resolution, which is a natural language processing task, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) the most likely category. The use of neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing and machine learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of features and logistic regression, which are also commonly used in computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a less likely but still possible category.
